we can't pull prints from bare skin

30:49.514 --> 30:51.766
then you must have smoked up a fatty.

30:51.850 --> 30:54.018
Or you're just extra dumb or both.

30:54.352 --> 30:56.521
-Did we pull prints from her skin?
-No. No, we did not.

30:56.604 --> 30:59.941
Okay, I grabbed her
and I tried to French kiss her.

31:00.024 --> 31:02.777
-French kiss? Like from the '80s?
-Yeah.

31:02.861 --> 31:05.572
But she wasn't down,
so, I just asked her for a hickie.

31:05.655 --> 31:07.824
Just so I'd have something
to show the dudes on Monday.

31:07.907 --> 31:09.617
Are you a real person?

31:10.493 --> 31:14.497
Look, Cassie was all upset about
her mom dying a couple of months ago

31:14.581 --> 31:16.541
and she was acting all weird, okay.

31:17.125 --> 31:20.837
Girl was rubbing sunscreen on herself
on a party bus at night.

31:20.920 --> 31:22.297
I mean, who does that?

31:22.380 --> 31:23.423
Sunscreen...

31:24.674 --> 31:27.844
-Analgesic.
-Cool. Analgesic.

31:28.177 --> 31:29.888
-What?
-It's a topical pain reliever.

31:29.971 --> 31:31.723
I think I know why the inside
of Cassie's body

31:31.806 --> 31:32.974
doesn't match the outside.

31:34.684 --> 31:37.437
I ran the blood splits
and you were right. Hemophilia.

31:37.520 --> 31:39.522
-Which is weird 'cause that's...
-Very rare in females.

31:39.606 --> 31:41.524
Yeah, less than
a one percent chance.

31:41.608 --> 31:43.192
No wonder it didn't show
in her records.

31:43.276 --> 31:44.986
She must have been
recently diagnosed here in Miami.

31:45.069 --> 31:47.530
And now we know why
her internal wounds are so extreme.

31:47.614 --> 31:48.698
Right.

31:48.781 --> 31:51.159
Abnormal bleeding
because of the blood disorder...

31:52.118 --> 31:54.162
Mitchie, did Cassie's mother
have the same disease?

31:54.245 --> 31:56.080
Not according to our medical records.

31:56.164 --> 31:59.250
And the high set comes through
in the clutch. No big deal.

31:59.334 --> 32:02.170
The hair fibers we found on Cassie,
not from the badger.

32:02.253 --> 32:05.256
But they were from an animal.
Just not a live one.

32:05.840 --> 32:07.467
It's chemically treated sheep's wool.

32:08.134 --> 32:10.470
-You're welcome.
-Sheep's wool?

32:12.597 --> 32:14.390
-Wow...
-Wow?

32:14.724 --> 32:16.017
Lane didn't do it.

32:16.976 --> 32:18.686
This is big.

32:26.069 --> 32:29.405
I got something good.

32:29.489 --> 32:31.407
Ladies first. Stop it.

32:31.491 --> 32:33.660
Cassie was exchanging emails
with Susan Sanchez,

32:33.743 --> 32:35.662
the reporter from Box
about meeting today.

32:35.745 --> 32:38.122
She said, that Cassie promised
that her story was explosive.

32:38.206 --> 32:40.291
I'm thinking we were right
about the mayor having an affair.

32:40.375 --> 32:42.961
And I'm thinking we were
wrong about the affair.

32:43.044 --> 32:44.545
-Are you sure?
-Positive.

32:44.629 --> 32:48.216
They weren't lovers.
Mayor Esparza was Cassie's father.

32:54.806 --> 32:57.600
So, Cassie had a rare form of
hemophilia. Her mother didn't have it,

32:57.684 --> 32:59.394
so I believe she inherited it
from her dad.

32:59.477 --> 33:01.270
And you think
Mayor Esparza has this disease.

33:01.354 --> 33:04.482
I do. But I have to get a look at his
upper torso and lower body to be sure.

33:04.983 --> 33:07.694
Doctor, I'm no doctor, but
I'm pretty sure that's the whole body.

33:07.777 --> 33:08.778
It is.

33:08.861 --> 33:11.531
Great. Should I ask the mayor
to swing by and get naked in the pen?

33:11.614 --> 33:12.949
You know what we should do?

33:13.032 --> 33:15.076
We should all get naked.
Make it less weird for him.

33:15.159 --> 33:18.162
Well, Captain, we know Cassie was
about to go to the press,

33:18.246 --> 33:21.249
maybe she was gonna tell the world she
was the mayor's illegitimate child.

33:21.332 --> 33:23.084
All right, should we draw straws

33:23.167 --> 33:25.628
to see who gets to drag the major
into an interrogation room?

33:25.712 --> 33:27.338
Well, you don't gotta
drag him anywhere.

33:27.422 --> 33:29.132
Best place to question him,
on his own turf,

33:29.215 --> 33:30.550
and I should be the one to do it.

33:31.384 --> 33:33.344
I love the short straw.
What do you say, Captain?

33:34.679 --> 33:37.473
-I don't hate this plan.
-I do, and I'll interrogate the mayor.

33:38.725 --> 33:42.729
We both know it's a bad idea for you
to it for so many reasons, don't we?

33:43.229 --> 33:45.148
The day I let politics stop me
from doing my job

33:45.231 --> 33:46.441
is the day I stop being a cop.

33:46.524 --> 33:48.109
Look, I get a confession, case closed.

33:48.192 --> 33:50.820
I don't, maybe one less bald guy
you got in the basement.

33:53.281 --> 33:54.365
Do what you got to do.

33:56.492 --> 33:58.161
Anything I should know before I go?

34:02.832 --> 34:04.542
Ira, I barely knew this girl.

34:05.668 --> 34:07.962
Big secrets have a way
of biting you in the ass.

34:08.046 --> 34:09.380
Believe me, I know.

34:09.464 --> 34:11.591
Mr. Mayor, you looked out for me.

34:11.674 --> 34:14.886
You know how much I care
about this job, the city.

34:15.470 --> 34:17.013
We're the same that way.

34:17.096 --> 34:18.222
I wanna look in your eyes

34:18.306 --> 34:20.600
the same way you looked in mine
a couple of weeks back,

34:21.601 --> 34:22.769
and hear the truth.

34:24.062 --> 34:26.022
You think I killed Cassie?

34:26.105 --> 34:28.316
The man I know
could never do something like that.

34:28.691 --> 34:30.610
And I'm praying right now
that you didn't.

34:31.694 --> 34:32.695
Ask away.

34:33.821 --> 34:36.491
You have an image, pristine,

34:36.574 --> 34:38.451
Senate run coming up,
that you got in the bag.

34:39.035 --> 34:40.870
I mean, there's no stopping
a rock star like you

34:40.953 --> 34:42.955
from laying his head once
where Obama laid his.

34:44.290 --> 34:48.503
But a media blitz about an affair,
having a child out of wedlock,

34:49.837 --> 34:51.547
that could jeopardize everything.

34:51.631 --> 34:54.050
What are you asking for? DNA?

34:54.133 --> 34:55.343
I don't need it.

34:56.469 --> 34:59.138
Cassie had something called
T-cranial hemophilia,

34:59.680 --> 35:01.224
likely inherited from her father.

35:03.518 --> 35:06.604
You mind rolling up your sleeve so
I can check an inter-vascular port?

35:07.396 --> 35:09.357
You get a lot of
blood transfusions, yeah?

35:13.653 --> 35:15.279
When Cassie's mother died,

35:16.322 --> 35:17.406
she found some letters,

35:18.449 --> 35:19.826
discovered I was her father.

35:21.160 --> 35:22.245
She contacted me,

35:22.328 --> 35:24.372
I was open
to having a relationship with her.

35:25.540 --> 35:28.960
I just asked her if she could
keep it a secret till after elections.

35:30.336 --> 35:31.337
She agreed.

35:31.838 --> 35:33.381
So why was she gonna go to the press?

35:34.173 --> 35:35.341
What are you talking about?

35:35.424 --> 35:38.761
Sheep's wool from this rug
was found on her body.

35:38.845 --> 35:40.513
She visited you hours before she died.

35:40.596 --> 35:42.974
I'm thinking to tell you
she was gonna spill the beans.

35:43.057 --> 35:44.767
Do not lie to me.

35:44.851 --> 35:47.979
I swear, if she was in my office
yesterday, I didn't see her.

35:48.062 --> 35:50.815
So you were at home with Linda
at the time of Cassie's murder?

35:53.484 --> 35:56.154
Your long-suffering wife
still covering a few bad habits?

35:57.572 --> 35:58.573
Who were you with?

35:59.657 --> 36:01.284
Hannah Connor, my assistant.

36:03.953 --> 36:05.997
So, am I in the clear?

36:08.708 --> 36:11.502
You know, I kept a lot of secrets
for my children's sake,

36:11.752 --> 36:14.297
but your secret might be the reason
why your daughter was murdered.

36:14.380 --> 36:15.923
So, yeah, I think you're in the clear.

36:17.884 --> 36:19.677
But I can't say the same
for your conscience.

36:24.223 --> 36:26.058
Hey, Cap.
You're gonna want to hear this.

36:27.685 --> 36:30.021
Okay, the mayor didn't kill Cassie.

36:30.104 --> 36:32.064
Came clean with his alibi
and it checked out.

36:32.648 --> 36:35.860
I'd take your word for it,
but you guys are friends, yeah?

36:36.235 --> 36:38.446
Look, it's all here.
Listen for yourself.

36:39.739 --> 36:42.491
I'm hungry. Anybody want anything?
I'm buying.

36:42.950 --> 36:45.286
-Honey bun and a cup of coffee.
-Honey bun?

36:46.579 --> 36:49.123
All right. But get your own coffee.

36:51.167 --> 36:53.211
So, what now? We got nothing?

36:53.294 --> 36:55.129
Actually no, we do have something.

36:55.213 --> 36:56.714
Cassie's hemophilia wasn't discovered

36:56.797 --> 36:59.091
until she took a paternity test
in Miami a few months ago.

36:59.175 --> 37:01.552
Meaning, only a few people would've known
that a fall down the stairs

37:01.636 --> 37:03.221
would be fatal
because of her condition.

37:03.304 --> 37:05.014
And of all the people
in the mayor's inner circle...

37:05.097 --> 37:06.390
Only one doesn't have an alibi.

37:06.474 --> 37:07.725
I think I know who the killer is.

37:07.808 --> 37:09.727
Me, too.
But we have no smoking gun.

37:10.519 --> 37:11.729
Or do we?

37:11.812 --> 37:12.813
Come on!

37:18.194 --> 37:20.488
Attie, I can't see the image clearly.
Clean it up.

37:20.571 --> 37:22.573
-You're making me nervous.
-Villa, it's your tone.

37:22.657 --> 37:23.824
Yes, it's your tone.

37:23.908 --> 37:26.702
Now can you please tighten up on the
fuzzy stuff and focus in on the eyes?

37:28.079 --> 37:29.705
Now that's how you talk to people.

37:32.250 --> 37:33.542
And there's our killer.

37:38.214 --> 37:40.466
-Rosey, you know what's kinda crazy?
-What's that, Villa?

37:40.549 --> 37:42.385
-Technology.
-Really? Crazy how?

37:42.468 --> 37:44.887
Well, say a killer
smashed his victim's phone,

37:44.971 --> 37:48.599
but in the process, it accidentally
snapped a picture of his twisted face.

37:48.683 --> 37:50.184
-What?
-Yep.

37:50.268 --> 37:52.561
Then you get Attie over here,
a gifted tech genius...

37:52.645 --> 37:54.272
-That's me.
-Put your hand down.

37:54.689 --> 37:57.400
Attie over here
does a bunch of nerdy stuff, and...

37:57.483 --> 37:59.694
Boom. You find this.

38:01.237 --> 38:02.613
This came from Cassie's phone.

38:03.447 --> 38:05.241
We knew you were there
when she went down those stairs.

38:05.324 --> 38:06.659
Which means you were the one
that killed her.

38:06.742 --> 38:09.745
You knew about her hemophilia,
discovered after her paternity test.

38:09.829 --> 38:11.539
You also knew that a fall
down the stairs

38:11.622 --> 38:13.708
for someone in Cassie's condition
could prove fatal.

38:13.791 --> 38:15.668
James, you want to explain this?

38:17.211 --> 38:19.839
She threatened you.
She was going to ruin your reputation.

38:20.298 --> 38:21.549
Our future.

38:21.924 --> 38:25.177
In two election cycles,
I'll be in the White House.

38:26.721 --> 38:28.306
She refused to keep her mouth shut

38:28.389 --> 38:30.516
and I didn't think
anyone was gonna miss her.

38:30.683 --> 38:32.476
We didn't think you'd step
right into our trap.

38:32.560 --> 38:35.229
See, James, we didn't need
a smoking gun to nail you.

38:35.313 --> 38:36.314
So we created our own.

38:36.397 --> 38:37.898
There was no image on Cassie's phone.

38:37.982 --> 38:39.984
But it didn't take long
for Attie to mock one up.

38:40.526 --> 38:43.029
-You can't do that.
-Actually, I think we just did do that.

38:43.112 --> 38:44.405
And you're done.

38:48.784 --> 38:51.329
Mayor Esparza, are you okay?

38:51.662 --> 38:53.622
No, I'm not.

38:54.332 --> 38:57.126
I'll never get a chance to say
everything I wanted to say to Cassie,

38:58.294 --> 38:59.378
to make amends,

39:01.422 --> 39:02.923
have a relationship with her.

39:05.176 --> 39:07.345
I don't think I could
ever forgive myself for that.

39:07.678 --> 39:10.765
You're right. You'll never know
how amazing your daughter really was.

39:12.558 --> 39:13.809
And that's your fault.

39:18.564 --> 39:20.941
Don't ever forgive yourself. Okay?

39:35.956 --> 39:38.417
Ira, what are you doing in here?

39:39.001 --> 39:41.587
Just admiring what you've done
with the place.

39:42.713 --> 39:44.340
You know, this doesn't
have to be painful.

39:45.132 --> 39:46.842
Yeah, it does.

39:48.052 --> 39:49.553
Who's the kid?

39:51.555 --> 39:53.099
That's me.

39:53.516 --> 39:55.935
I recognized the building.
Hillside at Lenox.

39:56.018 --> 39:58.729
St. Mel's Home for boys.
You were coming or going?

40:01.107 --> 40:02.274
It's going.

40:05.194 --> 40:06.487
Hmm.

40:11.033 --> 40:12.451
Okay.

40:38.853 --> 40:40.396
-I prefer Darjeeling.
-Okay.

40:40.479 --> 40:42.106
And you prefer talking to Pippy

40:42.189 --> 40:43.983
about things
that are happening in your life,

40:44.066 --> 40:46.777
but I kinda turned hers upside down

40:46.861 --> 40:51.240
and sent her to a hiding place
far, far away.

40:51.949 --> 40:54.034
Maybe a friend's house
down the street.

40:54.743 --> 40:56.245
Either way, my fault.

40:56.328 --> 40:58.164
Tara, listen to me--

40:58.247 --> 41:00.666
You have always been there for me
when I needed you.

41:00.749 --> 41:02.084
Shoulder to cry on,

41:02.418 --> 41:05.129
words of wisdom, you're my rock.

41:06.464 --> 41:07.756
And now I'm here to be yours.

41:08.466 --> 41:10.050
No matter what.

41:16.932 --> 41:18.184
Mmm!

41:18.267 --> 41:19.560
Oh, my God, that's terrible.

41:21.312 --> 41:22.813
-Tea?
-Mmm-hmm.

41:23.522 --> 41:24.982
Yes, please. Why did I do that?

41:26.901 --> 41:30.613
I'm making room
Inside my heart

41:31.071 --> 41:34.492
I'm moving on

41:35.117 --> 41:38.954
Look past the moon
Look past the stars

41:39.413 --> 41:43.959
I'm moving on
Moving on

42:00.392 --> 42:02.228
-Hey.
-Hey.

42:02.937 --> 42:05.064
-I was--
-You're not gonna let me in?

42:13.864 --> 42:15.616
-Villa...
-Please, don't.

42:36.679 --> 42:38.514
The two leads in your trash
are dead ends.

42:39.265 --> 42:40.724
That's everything I have so far.

42:41.433 --> 42:43.394
I'm gonna find out who killed Eddie.

42:43.477 --> 42:45.396
And I just want to say thank you

42:46.397 --> 42:48.649
for this, for what you've done.

42:48.732 --> 42:50.234
Because you know what? I...

42:52.152 --> 42:53.862
I may have never found out.

42:55.197 --> 42:57.116
But I don't want you
getting caught up--

42:57.199 --> 42:58.450
I'm in.

43:02.746 --> 43:04.582
I don't know what I'll do
when I catch them,

43:04.832 --> 43:05.666
and I can't have you--

43:05.749 --> 43:08.752
Villa, there's no way in hell
that I'm not with you on this one.

43:11.005 --> 43:12.381
Okay.

43:19.054 --> 43:21.473
-Let's get to work.
-Let's get to work.
